Rounding: Rounding is used to reduce the number of decimal places in a number to make it easier to read, compare, or report.
Rounding is applied when:
 You want to clean up messy decimal numbers.
 You want consistent data formats.
 You're working with prices, percentages, or scientific values.
To Access Rounding: Transform tab → Rounding (Dropdown) (Only appears when a numeric column is selected)
Example:
Trigonometric & Scientific Operations:
Although not commonly used in every business scenario, trigonometric and scientific functions in Power Query are helpful for:
1. Advanced calculations in technical, engineering, scientific, or academic data.
2. Transforming or generating values based on mathematical rules.
3. Supporting real-world measurements, like GPS coordinates, angles, time-series modeling, etc.
Information Operations:
These functions help in checking or identifying characteristics of numbers, such as whether a number is:
 Odd or Even
 Positive or Negative
